{
    "esm": "0.4.0",
    "metadata": {
        "name": "AdjustedLayerThickness",
        "description": "Adjusted top layer thickness for pervious and impervious road surfaces in the urban canopy thermal scheme. The adjustment compensates for the offset between the layer-averaged temperature carried by the finite-volume soil column and the surface temperature used in the surface-energy-balance kernel, using the tunable Yang (1998) coefficient c_a = 0.34. Migrated from UrbanCanopy.jl@9200edd4 src/roof_wall_road_snow_temperatures.jl:601 (`AdjustedLayerThickness` @component). Implements Oleson et al. (2010, CLM Tech Note Ch. 4) Eq. 4.30. Parameterized as observed-only: z_i, z_h_im1, z_ip1, c_a are inputs (parameters); Δz_star is the algebraic output.",
        "tags": [
            "urban_canopy",
            "temps",
            "geometry",
            "thermal",
            "observed-only",
            "clmu"
        ],
        "created": "2026-05-12T00:00:00Z",
        "authors": [
            "UrbanCanopy.jl contributors",
            "EarthSciModels migration (esm-i91d)"
        ],
        "references": [
            {
                "citation": "Oleson, K. W., et al. (2010). Technical Description of version 4.0 of the Community Land Model (CLM). NCAR Technical Note NCAR/TN-478+STR. Chapter 4, Section 4.3 (Roof, wall, and road temperatures), Eq. 4.30, p. 98."
            },
            {
                "citation": "Yang, Z.-L. (1998). Investigation of impacts of vegetation cover on regional climate. Ph.D. dissertation, University of Tokyo. (Source of the c_a = 0.34 tuning coefficient used in Eq. 4.30.)"
            }
        ]
    },
    "models": {
        "AdjustedLayerThickness": {
            "reference": {
                "notes": "source_ref: UrbanCanopy.jl@9200edd4f15609f20339d3a7d104de8064544310:src/roof_wall_road_snow_temperatures.jl:601\nUpstream `AdjustedLayerThickness` is an MTK `@component` whose three geometry inputs (z_i, z_h_im1, z_ip1) are `@parameters` and whose single output (Δz_star) is a time-indexed `@variable` with one algebraic equation (Eq. 4.30). Identical equation structure preserved here.\n\nThe upstream component declares one `@constant`: c_a = 0.34 (dimensionless tunable coefficient from Yang 1998). It is encoded here as a fixed-default parameter with the upstream value, matching the convention used by sibling observed-only ESM files in this rig that translate `@constants` to parameters (snow_soil_blended_heat_capacity.esm encodes C_ice the same way, snow_melt_no_layers.esm encodes L_f, zero_kgm2, zero_m the same way).\n\nUnicode `Δz_star` (adjusted top layer thickness) is preserved from upstream — the schema's identifier pattern allows it and other ESM components in this rig already use unicode delta in identifiers (e.g. snow_soil_blended_heat_capacity.esm uses `Δz`, snow_melt_no_layers.esm uses `Δt`).\n\nObservability classification: this component is functionally observed-only — the single output variable is given by a single algebraic equation in terms of the parameters (and the `(t)` time index has no role since there is no derivative). Test scenarios use `time_span: [0, 1]` and sample at t=0 to mirror the convention used by sibling observed-only ESM files (snow_soil_blended_heat_capacity.esm, snow_melt_no_layers.esm, total_phase_change_energy.esm).\n\nTolerance rationale (model-level rel=1e-10): observed-only single-equation algebraic system (no ODE integration); the equation is two subtractions, one multiplication, one addition, and one halving, so roundoff is at the IEEE-754 ULP level (~1e-16). The upstream tests use `rtol = 1.0e-10` (test/roof_wall_road_snow_temperatures_test.jl:566) and we mirror that for fidelity. Tighter `abs: 1e-9` is asserted on outputs that are exactly zero by construction (degenerate equal-z case) so the assertion does not silently accept a stuck-at-zero regression."
            },
            "tolerance": {
                "rel": 1.0e-10
            },
            "variables": {
                "z_i": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m",
                    "default": 0.0,
                    "description": "Node depth of top layer i (depth at which the layer-averaged temperature is carried)"
                },
                "z_h_im1": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m",
                    "default": 0.0,
                    "description": "Interface depth above layer i (z_{h,i-1} — the upper boundary of the top layer, i.e. the surface for a surface-layer column where z_h_im1 = 0)"
                },
                "z_ip1": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m",
                    "default": 0.0,
                    "description": "Node depth of layer i+1 (the second-from-top layer used in the Eq. 4.30 averaging stencil)"
                },
                "c_a": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "1",
                    "default": 0.34,
                    "description": "Tunable Yang (1998) coefficient. Dimensionless. Default 0.34 from Oleson Eq. 4.30."
                },
                "Δz_star": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "m",
                    "description": "Adjusted top layer thickness (Oleson Eq. 4.30): 0.5 * (z_i - z_h_im1 + c_a * (z_ip1 - z_h_im1))"
                }
            },
            "equations": [
                {
                    "lhs": "Δz_star",
                    "rhs": {
                        "op": "*",
                        "args": [
                            0.5,
                            {
                                "op": "+",
                                "args": [
                                    {
                                        "op": "-",
                                        "args": ["z_i", "z_h_im1"]
                                    },
                                    {
                                        "op": "*",
                                        "args": [
                                            "c_a",
                                            {
                                                "op": "-",
                                                "args": ["z_ip1", "z_h_im1"]
                                            }
                                        ]
                                    }
                                ]
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                }
            ],
            "tests": [
                {
                    "id": "upstream_equation_verification",
                    "description": "Reproduces upstream `AdjustedLayerThickness - Equation Verification` test (UrbanCanopy.jl test/roof_wall_road_snow_temperatures_test.jl:546-567). Inputs: z_i = 0.05 m, z_h_im1 = 0.0 m, z_ip1 = 0.15 m, c_a = 0.34. Expected Δz_star = 0.5 * (0.05 - 0.0 + 0.34 * (0.15 - 0.0)) = 0.5 * 0.101 = 0.0505 m. Anchors fidelity to the upstream Julia component at the same parameter values.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "z_i": 0.05,
                        "z_h_im1": 0.0,
                        "z_ip1": 0.15
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        { "variable": "Δz_star", "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.0505 }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "upstream_positive_output",
                    "description": "Reproduces upstream `AdjustedLayerThickness - Positive Output` test (UrbanCanopy.jl test/roof_wall_road_snow_temperatures_test.jl:569-584). With a typical road geometry (z_i = 0.1, z_h_im1 = 0.0, z_ip1 = 0.3), the adjusted thickness is 0.5 * (0.1 + 0.34 * 0.3) = 0.5 * 0.202 = 0.101 m. Upstream only asserts >0; this entry pins the exact expected value so any sign-flip or coefficient regression is caught.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "z_i": 0.1,
                        "z_h_im1": 0.0,
                        "z_ip1": 0.3
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        { "variable": "Δz_star", "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.101 }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "nonzero_upper_interface",
                    "description": "Sub-surface layer geometry with a non-zero upper interface (z_h_im1 = 0.02 m): z_i = 0.05, z_ip1 = 0.20, c_a = 0.34. Expected Δz_star = 0.5 * (0.05 - 0.02 + 0.34 * (0.20 - 0.02)) = 0.5 * (0.03 + 0.0612) = 0.5 * 0.0912 = 0.0456 m. Exercises the full subtraction structure of Eq. 4.30 — the upstream tests only cover z_h_im1 = 0 (top-surface) cases.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "z_i": 0.05,
                        "z_h_im1": 0.02,
                        "z_ip1": 0.20
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        { "variable": "Δz_star", "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.0456 }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "degenerate_equal_z",
                    "description": "Degenerate geometry where all three depths are equal (z_i = z_h_im1 = z_ip1 = 0.1): both differences in Eq. 4.30 vanish, so Δz_star = 0 exactly. Confirms the equation collapses to zero in the trivial case and catches any spurious additive offset.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "z_i": 0.1,
                        "z_h_im1": 0.1,
                        "z_ip1": 0.1
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        { "variable": "Δz_star", "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.0, "tolerance": { "abs": 1.0e-12 } }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "c_a_zero_override",
                    "description": "Override c_a = 0 (drops the Yang correction term): Δz_star reduces to the plain half-layer thickness 0.5 * (z_i - z_h_im1). At z_i = 0.04, z_h_im1 = 0.0, z_ip1 = 0.12 the expected value is 0.5 * 0.04 = 0.02 m. Exercises the c_a-as-parameter override path and confirms the Yang-coefficient term is what it claims to be.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "z_i": 0.04,
                        "z_h_im1": 0.0,
                        "z_ip1": 0.12,
                        "c_a": 0.0
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        { "variable": "Δz_star", "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.02 }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "c_a_unity_override",
                    "description": "Override c_a = 1 (full Yang weight): Δz_star = 0.5 * (z_i + z_ip1 - 2*z_h_im1). At z_i = 0.05, z_h_im1 = 0.0, z_ip1 = 0.15 the expected value is 0.5 * (0.05 + 0.15) = 0.10 m — the simple symmetric midpoint thickness. Pairs with `c_a_zero_override` to bracket the tuning-coefficient sensitivity.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "z_i": 0.05,
                        "z_h_im1": 0.0,
                        "z_ip1": 0.15,
                        "c_a": 1.0
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        { "variable": "Δz_star", "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.1 }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "deep_subgrade",
                    "description": "Deep subgrade layer geometry representative of mid-column CLM levels (z_i = 1.0 m, z_h_im1 = 0.6 m, z_ip1 = 1.5 m, c_a = 0.34). Expected Δz_star = 0.5 * (1.0 - 0.6 + 0.34 * (1.5 - 0.6)) = 0.5 * (0.4 + 0.306) = 0.5 * 0.706 = 0.353 m. Exercises the equation away from the surface-layer regime covered by the upstream tests.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "z_i": 1.0,
                        "z_h_im1": 0.6,
                        "z_ip1": 1.5
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        { "variable": "Δz_star", "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.353 }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "intermediate_layer",
                    "description": "Intermediate-depth layer geometry with non-zero upper interface and substantial spacing to layer i+1 (z_i = 0.3, z_h_im1 = 0.1, z_ip1 = 0.7, c_a = 0.34): Δz_star = 0.5 * (0.3 - 0.1 + 0.34 * (0.7 - 0.1)) = 0.5 * (0.2 + 0.204) = 0.5 * 0.404 = 0.202 m. Provides a third independent (z_i, z_h_im1, z_ip1) triple in the typical CLM road-column range, complementing `nonzero_upper_interface` and `deep_subgrade`.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "z_i": 0.3,
                        "z_h_im1": 0.1,
                        "z_ip1": 0.7
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        { "variable": "Δz_star", "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.202 }
                    ]
                }
            ],
            "examples": [
                {
                    "id": "delta_z_star_vs_z_ip1",
                    "description": "Sweep the node depth of layer i+1 across a typical CLM road-column range (0.05 m to 1.0 m) at fixed z_i = 0.05 m, z_h_im1 = 0.0 m, c_a = 0.34. Δz_star = 0.5 * (z_i + c_a * z_ip1) is a line of slope 0.5 * c_a = 0.17 above the intercept 0.5 * z_i = 0.025 m, surfacing the linear sensitivity of the adjusted thickness to the spacing of the second-from-top layer per Eq. 4.30.",
                    "initial_state": {
                        "type": "per_variable",
                        "values": {}
                    },
                    "parameters": {
                        "z_i": 0.05,
                        "z_h_im1": 0.0
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "parameter_sweep": {
                        "type": "cartesian",
                        "dimensions": [
                            {
                                "parameter": "z_ip1",
                                "range": { "start": 0.05, "stop": 1.0, "count": 11, "scale": "linear" }
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    "plots": [
                        {
                            "id": "delta_z_star_curve",
                            "type": "line",
                            "description": "Δz_star vs z_ip1: linear rise of slope 0.5*c_a above the 0.5*z_i baseline per Eq. 4.30.",
                            "x": { "variable": "z_ip1",   "label": "z_{i+1} (m)" },
                            "y": { "variable": "Δz_star", "label": "Δz_star (m)" }
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "two_d_sweep_zi_zip1",
                    "description": "Joint sweep over z_i and z_ip1 at fixed z_h_im1 = 0.0 m and c_a = 0.34. Δz_star = 0.5 * (z_i + c_a * z_ip1) is a plane in (z_i, z_ip1) with slope 0.5 along z_i and slope 0.5 * c_a = 0.17 along z_ip1, so iso-Δz_star contours are straight lines z_i + 0.34 * z_ip1 = const. Maps the adjusted thickness across the CLM road-layer geometry plane.",
                    "initial_state": {
                        "type": "per_variable",
                        "values": {}
                    },
                    "parameters": {
                        "z_h_im1": 0.0
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "parameter_sweep": {
                        "type": "cartesian",
                        "dimensions": [
                            {
                                "parameter": "z_i",
                                "range": { "start": 0.02, "stop": 0.5, "count": 11, "scale": "linear" }
                            },
                            {
                                "parameter": "z_ip1",
                                "range": { "start": 0.05, "stop": 1.0, "count": 11, "scale": "linear" }
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    "plots": [
                        {
                            "id": "delta_z_star_heatmap",
                            "type": "heatmap",
                            "description": "Δz_star as a function of top-layer node depth z_i and next-layer node depth z_ip1: linear plane with straight iso-Δz_star contours per Eq. 4.30.",
                            "x": { "variable": "z_i",   "label": "z_i (m)" },
                            "y": { "variable": "z_ip1", "label": "z_{i+1} (m)" },
                            "value": { "variable": "Δz_star", "reduce": "final" }
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "c_a_sensitivity",
                    "description": "Sensitivity of the adjusted thickness to the Yang (1998) tuning coefficient c_a, swept from 0 (drops the Yang term) to 1 (full symmetric midpoint thickness) at fixed road-surface geometry (z_i = 0.05, z_h_im1 = 0.0, z_ip1 = 0.15). Δz_star = 0.5 * (z_i + c_a * z_ip1) traces a line from 0.025 m at c_a = 0 up to 0.10 m at c_a = 1, with the upstream default c_a = 0.34 landing at 0.0505 m (matching the `upstream_equation_verification` test).",
                    "initial_state": {
                        "type": "per_variable",
                        "values": {}
                    },
                    "parameters": {
                        "z_i": 0.05,
                        "z_h_im1": 0.0,
                        "z_ip1": 0.15
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "parameter_sweep": {
                        "type": "cartesian",
                        "dimensions": [
                            {
                                "parameter": "c_a",
                                "range": { "start": 0.0, "stop": 1.0, "count": 11, "scale": "linear" }
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    "plots": [
                        {
                            "id": "c_a_sensitivity_curve",
                            "type": "line",
                            "description": "Δz_star vs c_a: linear ramp from 0.5*z_i at c_a=0 up to the symmetric midpoint 0.5*(z_i + z_ip1) at c_a=1 per Eq. 4.30.",
                            "x": { "variable": "c_a",     "label": "c_a (dimensionless)" },
                            "y": { "variable": "Δz_star", "label": "Δz_star (m)" }
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        }
    }
}
